\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/cmf.maximal}{Maximal newform}}
\begin{definition*}\label{cmf.maximal}
\uses{cmf.character,cmf.dimension,cmf.galois_orbit,cmf.newform}
A \hyperref[cmf.newform]{newform} is \textbf{maximal} if its \hyperref[cmf.galois_orbit]{Galois orbit} spans the ambient subspace that contains it (its \hyperref[cmf.atkin_lehner_dims]{Atkin-Lehner subspace} when the \hyperref[cmf.character]{character} is trivial, the entire newspace otherwise).

A newform is the \textbf{largest} newform in its ambient subspace if its \hyperref[cmf.dimension]{dimension} is strictly larger than that of any other newform in the same subspace (this includes newforms that are maximal).
\end{definition*}


